<div id="review_61268596" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/61268596" />
    <a title="Agnieszka" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2446508-agnieszka"><img alt="Agnieszka" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1371835955p2/2446508.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/61268596?book_show_action=true">Jun 27, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Agnieszka" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Agnieszka" href="/user/show/2446508-agnieszka">Agnieszka</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2446508-agnieszka?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2446508-agnieszka?shelf=1001-books">1001-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2446508-agnieszka?shelf=own-a-copy">own-a-copy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2446508-agnieszka?shelf=2014">2014</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2446508-agnieszka?shelf=i-saw-the-movie-too">i-saw-the-movie-too</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer61268596" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12278201409533222629"><br/><i>When everything goes wrong, what a joy to test your soul and see if it has endurance and courage! An invisible and all-powerful enemy - some call him God, others the Devil, seems to rush upon us to destroy us; but we are not destroyed .</i><br/><br/>Story set in Cretan scenery – imagine raw landscape, composed of granite and limestone ; silvery olives, figs and vine plants, orange groves, scent of sage and mint, the vast expanse of the sea and an emerald islands in the distance, bathed in sunlight. There’s no</span>
  <span id="freeText12278201409533222629" style="display:none"><br><i>When everything goes wrong, what a joy to test your soul and see if it has endurance and courage! An invisible and all-powerful enemy - some call him God, others the Devil, seems to rush upon us to destroy us; but we are not destroyed .</i><br><br>Story set in Cretan scenery – imagine raw landscape, composed of granite and limestone ; silvery olives, figs and vine plants, orange groves, scent of sage and mint, the vast expanse of the sea and an emerald islands in the distance, bathed in sunlight. There’s no other place where time flows so lazy. Greece, the cradle of civilization.<br> <br>Narrator, a bookworm who craves for real life, arrives here to manage a coal mine. Earlier in the port cafe he meets Zorba who offers him services. Men are different in almost everything: the origin, age, beliefs, temperament, religion, way of life. But so begins their friendship.<br><br>Zorba is one of the most life-affirming character in all literature I know. When we meet him he's a 65-year-old but young at heart man, who travelled far and wide, yearning for women, wine and life. On the other hand, he's a simple and sensitive person, able to admire the beauty of nature, who hides deeply own worries and anguish and is enjoying life. A man with zest for life, with his own philosophy of life "I act as if I was going to die at any moment” Banal ? What of it ?<br><br>This book is neither for telling nor reviewing. This book is for drinking and eating, for singing and dancing, for laughing and breathing. This book is for you could say when you’ve failed <i> That's nothing! Nothing to worry about </i>. This book is for you could on your death bed shout <i> I've done heaps and heaps of things in my life, but I still did not do enough. Men like me ought to live a thousand years. Good night!</i>. This book is for Life. <br><br>Teach me to dance , Zorba.<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1496229360i/22891863._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
  <a data-text-id="12278201409533222629" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


